<paragraph blockId="24.[227,1437,1442,1593]" pageId="24" pageNumber="34">
Genus of the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Becker &amp; House" authorityYear="1993" box="[489,645,1442,1468]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Koenenitidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="24" pageNumber="34" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Koenenitidae</taxonomicName>
with extremely discoidal, subinvolute to involute conch; venter rounded in all stages. Suture line with wide external lobe, moderately high median saddle, narrowly V-shaped E2 lobe, U-shaped or V-shaped lateral lobe and rounded umbilical lobes. Suture line formula (E 
<subScript attach="left" box="[254,263,1579,1593]" fontSize="6" pageId="24" pageNumber="34">2</subScript>
E 
<subScript attach="left" box="[288,297,1579,1593]" fontSize="6" pageId="24" pageNumber="34">1</subScript>
E 
<subScript attach="left" box="[322,331,1579,1593]" fontSize="6" pageId="24" pageNumber="34">2</subScript>
) L U 
<subScript attach="left" box="[393,402,1579,1593]" fontSize="6" pageId="24" pageNumber="34">2</subScript>
: U 
<subScript attach="left" box="[438,447,1579,1593]" fontSize="6" pageId="24" pageNumber="34">1</subScript>
I.
</paragraph>
